  "text": "The surge in internet usage and advertising revenues has attracted substantial academic inter- Research on search advertising has focused mainly on competition in advertising auctions and consumer search. [CITATION_1] analyzed a homogeneous products market organized by a search engine (\"gatekeeper\") and showed that the gatekeeper's incentive is to maximize consumer adoption but limit the number of advertisers using the platform since it can extract more revenues when competition among advertisers is lessened. [CITATION_2] analyzed optimal consumer search and advertiser bid strategies and showed that advertisers'bid order mirrors their products' relevance order. Consumers then optimally engage in sequential search. Edelman, Ostrovsky, and Schwarz (2007) and Varian (forthcoming) modeled the auction mechanisms used by search engines in extensive detail.",
